tures rather than discussing the one-pot method. The importance of the method is already described in the introductions section. However, direct evidence of the reaction mechanism is not available in the current mandate. ATR - FTIR spectrum of the HNF confirms the absence of organic contents from the source precursor reaction bath on it. We also found that the crystallographic and optical properties refer to the standard hematite phase and the absorption band of 550 nm. Finally, the photoelectrochemical performance of the films is affected by the combined influence of two different morphologies, both nanooctahedron and cauliflower. However, in both cases, it appears that photocurrent density of only cauliflower film deviates from that of nano octahedron with a higher order of magnitude at 50μA/cm2. The photocurrent density of the HNF is found to be increased up to 100 μA/cm2 validated a two-fold enhancement after beta carotene coating. It also helps to remove the cathodic transient spike, which is an essential finding in terms of physicochemical properties enhancement. The beta-carotene coated hematite films will be utilized further to understand the stability and efficiency enhancement with the fabrication of a bio photoelectrochemical device.
